00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:13.140
Bullseye.

00:04:13.140 --> 00:04:17.140
Okay, was that natural talent and acquired skill or just plain luck?

00:04:17.140 --> 00:04:18.140
You decide.

00:04:18.140 --> 00:04:21.140
You know, some things you're born good at, some things you get good at,

00:04:21.140 --> 00:04:24.140
and sometimes you have goodness thrust upon you.

00:04:25.140 --> 00:04:27.140
Here's an example of natural talent.

00:04:27.140 --> 00:04:30.140
My talent for shutting up my motor mouth brother.

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:32.140
Hey, what are you doing? That's no way to fold socks.

00:04:32.140 --> 00:04:33.140
The top part gets all stretchy.

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:35.140
There's a much better way to do that.

00:04:35.140 --> 00:04:36.140
I thought everybody knew that.

00:04:36.140 --> 00:04:38.140
First, you put them together.

00:04:38.140 --> 00:04:40.140
Then, you smooth them out.

00:04:40.140 --> 00:04:42.140
Then, you fold them over.

00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:46.140
Then, there are acquired skills.

00:04:46.140 --> 00:04:49.140
You know, the stuff that you actually have to work on to get good at,

00:04:49.140 --> 00:04:53.140
it's like knowing what to say when your dad presents his latest architectural wonder.

00:04:54.140 --> 00:04:56.140
I call it sneakers to go.

00:04:56.140 --> 00:04:58.140
What do you think?

00:04:58.140 --> 00:05:01.140
Gee, dad, it's really unique.

00:05:03.140 --> 00:05:05.140
Finally, there's that old standby.

00:05:06.140 --> 00:05:12.290
Hello.

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:14.290
Good old fashion luck.

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:19.290
I guess the point is, whether it's a gift, a skill, or just plain old luck,

00:05:19.290 --> 00:05:25.390
when you've got it, you've got it.

00:05:25.390 --> 00:06:21.930
The only question is, how do you get it back?

00:06:21.930 --> 00:06:24.930
Okay, I know this may sound odd, but for some strange reason,

00:06:24.930 --> 00:06:27.930
out of the blue, I've discovered the flute.

00:06:27.930 --> 00:06:29.930
I guess I mean rediscovered.

00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:31.930
It wasn't always this way.

00:06:31.930 --> 00:06:34.930
It all started two years ago when I had to take home act or band.

00:06:34.930 --> 00:06:36.930
Some choice.

00:06:36.930 --> 00:06:38.930
They didn't even have the instruments that I really wanted.

00:06:38.930 --> 00:06:41.930
Ah, Clarissa, we are out of trombones.

00:06:41.930 --> 00:06:45.930
Why don't you try the flute?

00:06:46.930 --> 00:06:49.930
I was assigned the Wimph of the Woodwind section.

00:06:49.930 --> 00:06:54.980
While I could only produce sounds no one could hear.

00:06:54.980 --> 00:07:00.090
No one on two legs, anyway.

00:07:02.090 --> 00:07:11.520
But after steady practice, I found myself today at 2 p.m.

00:07:11.520 --> 00:07:14.520
in Mrs. Doppelgeuse Music Class.

00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:16.520
All of a sudden, it felt good.

00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:18.520
Really good.

00:07:18.520 --> 00:07:21.520
Clarissa, that was beautiful.

00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:24.520
Oh, you have made a real breakthrough.

00:07:24.520 --> 00:07:26.520
Now we are going to have to do something

00:07:26.520 --> 00:07:30.520
with this amazing talent that you have been hiding.

00:07:32.800 --> 00:07:34.800
So now Mrs. Doppelgeuse has me performing a solo

00:07:34.800 --> 00:07:36.800
in the school recital next week.

00:07:36.800 --> 00:07:39.800
The weird thing is, I'm really psyched about it.

00:07:39.800 --> 00:07:41.800
It used to be I hated going to those things,

00:07:41.800 --> 00:07:43.800
forget about being in them.

00:07:43.800 --> 00:07:45.800
Still, lately I've been getting some strange thrill

00:07:45.800 --> 00:07:47.800
out of hitting those high notes,

00:07:47.800 --> 00:08:00.460
but it's still interesting.

00:08:00.460 --> 00:08:03.460
Clarissa? What kind of music are you listening to?

00:08:03.460 --> 00:08:06.460
Hey, I thought that was a CD.

00:08:06.460 --> 00:08:09.460
I'm getting really good, Clarissa.

00:08:09.460 --> 00:08:11.460
Clarissa.

00:08:11.460 --> 00:08:13.460
Oh, hi, Sam.

00:08:13.460 --> 00:08:14.460
Didn't you notice me?

00:08:14.460 --> 00:08:17.460
I guess not. I was playing and something clicked, I guess.

00:08:17.460 --> 00:08:19.460
I'll say, but classical?

00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:21.460
I know.

00:08:21.460 --> 00:08:23.460
Who'd have thought that guys in Wigs 300 years ago

00:08:23.460 --> 00:08:25.460
could write music so cool?

00:08:25.460 --> 00:08:27.460
Well, I just came over to give you back your 10,000

00:08:27.460 --> 00:08:29.460
Maniacs tape, but it sounds like

00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:31.460
your taste in music is changing, so...

00:08:31.460 --> 00:08:33.460
Not so fast, Sam.

00:08:33.460 --> 00:08:36.460
My taste in music is expanding, not changing.

00:08:36.460 --> 00:08:38.460
You can't blame me for trying.

00:08:38.460 --> 00:08:40.460
Just because I'm really into playing the flute

00:08:40.460 --> 00:08:45.240
doesn't mean I'm giving up guitars.

00:08:45.240 --> 00:08:46.240
What's that?

00:08:46.240 --> 00:08:48.240
Remote control for the toaster?

00:08:48.240 --> 00:08:51.240
No, Ferguson, I'm testing our appliances for EMS.

00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:53.240
EMS? The only appliance you're going to hear

00:08:53.240 --> 00:08:55.240
EMF on is the radio.

00:08:55.240 --> 00:08:57.240
Besides, they haven't had a new album out in a while.

00:08:57.240 --> 00:08:59.240
It's the electromagnetic field.

00:08:59.240 --> 00:09:01.240
I knew that.

00:09:01.240 --> 00:09:03.240
Some people think too much EMF exposure

00:09:03.240 --> 00:09:05.240
can pose a health risk, and we were talking

00:09:05.240 --> 00:09:07.240
about the museum, so I thought I'd check it out.

00:09:07.240 --> 00:09:11.240
Ah, so the toaster might be killing me.

00:09:11.240 --> 00:09:13.240
Well, I doubt it.

00:09:13.240 --> 00:09:15.240
But it would be nice to know we lived

00:09:15.240 --> 00:09:17.240
in a non-toxic environment.

00:09:17.240 --> 00:09:19.240
Non-toxic? You mean we're sending Ferguson away?

00:09:19.240 --> 00:09:21.240
Mom, Evan's to be testing for EMS,

00:09:21.240 --> 00:09:23.240
something I'm sure you've heard nothing about.

00:09:23.240 --> 00:09:25.240
I saw them live.

00:09:25.240 --> 00:09:27.240
EMS stands for...

00:09:27.240 --> 00:09:29.240
Electromagnetic fields?

00:09:29.240 --> 00:09:31.240
So, Mom, how much do one of these

00:09:31.240 --> 00:09:33.240
EMF detector things go for?

00:09:33.240 --> 00:09:35.240
Well, I borrowed this one from the Children's Museum,

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:37.240
but I think they cost a couple of hundred dollars.

00:09:37.240 --> 00:09:39.240
Ooh, the neighbors really should know about this,

00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:41.240
but they can't be expected to shell out

00:09:41.240 --> 00:09:47.210
a couple of hundred bucks a piece.

00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:49.210
Why should the neighbors pay for their

00:09:49.210 --> 00:09:51.210
own EMF testing kits

00:09:51.210 --> 00:09:53.210
when an expert can test their homes for them?

00:09:53.210 --> 00:09:55.210
And who might that expert be?

00:09:55.210 --> 00:09:57.210
Hmm, I don't know.

00:09:57.210 --> 00:09:59.210
I haven't given a much thought.

00:09:59.210 --> 00:10:01.210
Me?

00:10:01.210 --> 00:10:03.210
Oh, if you could start a neighborhood EMF watch.

00:10:03.210 --> 00:10:05.210
Hmm, I wonder how much it should charge as a fee.

00:10:05.210 --> 00:10:07.210
Oh, Ferguson.

00:10:07.210 --> 00:10:11.800
Clarissa, Mrs. Dobble do call about your flute solo.

00:10:11.800 --> 00:10:13.800
That's wonderful news.

00:10:13.800 --> 00:10:15.800
Yeah, usually I don't do that kind of thing,

00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:17.800
but this should be fun.

00:10:17.800 --> 00:10:19.800
I'm playing this really cool piece by Bach.

00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:21.800
Did I just use the words cool

00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:23.800
and Bach in the same sentence?

00:10:23.800 --> 00:10:25.800
It's happening to me.

00:10:25.800 --> 00:10:27.800
So, you're finally starting to enjoy the flute,

00:10:27.800 --> 00:10:29.800
right?

00:10:29.800 --> 00:10:31.800
Yeah, Dad, it was the weirdest thing.

00:10:31.800 --> 00:10:33.800
It was like two years of practice finally kicked in.

00:10:33.800 --> 00:10:35.800
My breath control,

00:10:35.800 --> 00:10:37.800
my fingering, my phrasing, they all work together.

00:10:37.800 --> 00:10:39.800
Usually I'm lucky to get two out of three.

00:10:39.800 --> 00:10:41.800
Her teacher said she has a real gift.

00:10:41.800 --> 00:10:43.800
Oh, well, that makes sense.

00:10:43.800 --> 00:10:45.800
Musicability runs in the family.

00:10:45.800 --> 00:10:47.800
I mean, I was a pretty fair drummer

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:49.800
back in college if I say so myself.

00:10:49.800 --> 00:10:51.800
Dad, you used to play the drums?

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:53.800
Beat them to death is more like it.

00:10:53.800 --> 00:10:55.800
He said it was releasing aggression.

00:10:55.800 --> 00:10:57.800
I would have put Ringo out of a job.

00:10:57.800 --> 00:11:03.700
I'm kind of glad Dad didn't stick with it.

00:11:03.700 --> 00:11:05.700
Why is that, Clarissa?

00:11:05.700 --> 00:11:07.700
Because then we'd have to deal with a new kind of EMF.

00:11:07.700 --> 00:11:09.700
Entertainment by middle-aged fathers.

00:11:09.700 --> 00:11:13.530
Sure, Sam, come by.

00:11:13.530 --> 00:11:15.530
I'll just be practicing my solo.

00:11:15.530 --> 00:11:17.530
Okay, see you later.

00:11:17.530 --> 00:11:21.770
Bye.

00:11:21.770 --> 00:11:23.770
Okay, I've put aside the whole morning to practice my piece.

00:11:23.770 --> 00:11:25.770
I figure if I memorize it today,

00:11:25.770 --> 00:11:27.770
I can just walk out on stage,

00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:29.770
no music, and just play.

00:11:29.770 --> 00:11:31.770
That'll blow them away.

00:11:31.770 --> 00:11:33.770
It's been a major morning of total focus.

00:11:33.770 --> 00:11:35.770
Undisturbed, uninterrupted.

00:11:35.770 --> 00:11:37.770
Hey, Sport.

00:11:37.770 --> 00:11:41.020
I, uh...

00:11:41.020 --> 00:11:43.020
I brought you something I'd like you to have.

00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:45.020
What's that, Dad?

00:11:45.020 --> 00:11:47.020
Oh, some sheet music back from when I was a musician.

00:11:47.020 --> 00:11:49.020
Yeah, we did some wicked Jethro Tell covers back then,

00:11:49.020 --> 00:11:51.020
and there's some stuff for the flute in there.

00:11:51.020 --> 00:11:53.020
Great.

00:11:53.020 --> 00:11:55.020
Yeah, it's great to see you so excited about your music

00:11:55.020 --> 00:11:57.020
that I'd hate to see you hang it up like I did.

00:11:57.020 --> 00:11:59.020
So, you know, maybe if you really stick with it,

00:11:59.020 --> 00:12:01.020
you could hit the big time, huh?

00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:03.020
Whoa, Dad, slow down.

00:12:03.020 --> 00:12:05.020
I don't even have my first gold record yet.

00:12:05.020 --> 00:12:07.020
It's just a school recital.

00:12:07.020 --> 00:12:09.020
Well, I just never know where it could lead.

00:12:09.020 --> 00:12:11.020
Where did Mozart get his start?

00:12:11.020 --> 00:12:13.020
Playing for the crowned heads of Europe.

00:12:13.020 --> 00:12:15.020
Well, yeah, I mean,

00:12:15.020 --> 00:12:17.020
that was sort of an 18th-century version of the school recital.

00:12:17.020 --> 00:12:19.020
I mean, everybody's got to start somewhere.

00:12:19.020 --> 00:12:26.490
Hey?

00:12:26.490 --> 00:12:28.490
No pressure there. Just top Mozart.

00:12:28.490 --> 00:12:32.120
Jethro Tell.

00:12:32.120 --> 00:12:34.120
Who's they?

00:12:34.120 --> 00:12:39.220
Oh, sword and drop-up.

00:12:39.220 --> 00:12:41.220
I'll tell you, though.

00:12:41.220 --> 00:12:43.220
Guests who Mrs. Doppel do invited to the recital.

00:12:43.220 --> 00:12:45.220
Jethro Tell?

00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:47.220
Close. Zoe Vanzinia Zanza.

00:12:47.220 --> 00:12:49.220
Zoe Vanzinia Zanza?

00:12:49.220 --> 00:12:51.220
Madam Zoe Vanzinia Zanza?

00:12:51.220 --> 00:12:53.220
She's the best flute instructor in the state.

00:12:53.220 --> 00:12:55.220
You know, she only takes one new student a year,

00:12:55.220 --> 00:12:57.220
and some of her students have gone on

00:12:57.220 --> 00:12:59.220
to play the finest symphony orchestras in the country.

00:12:59.220 --> 00:13:01.220
What's she want to see me for?

00:13:01.220 --> 00:13:03.220
Well, she'll be there to hear the whole recital,

00:13:03.220 --> 00:13:05.220
but I don't know how she could miss you

00:13:05.220 --> 00:13:07.220
performing the evening's only flute solo.

00:13:07.220 --> 00:13:09.220
Yeah, that would be kind of hard, wouldn't it?

00:13:09.220 --> 00:13:11.220
Wow.

00:13:11.220 --> 00:13:13.220
I guess I better start practicing already.

00:13:13.220 --> 00:13:22.460
I'm not quite ready for an audience.

00:13:22.460 --> 00:13:24.460
Oh, sorry.

00:13:24.460 --> 00:13:26.460
I'll wait till the concert.

00:13:26.460 --> 00:13:28.460
Recital.

00:13:28.460 --> 00:13:30.460
What's wrong with the word concert, Clarissa?

00:13:30.460 --> 00:13:32.460
Well, a concert is big and scary.

00:13:32.460 --> 00:13:34.460
Recital is intimate, manageable,

00:13:34.460 --> 00:13:36.460
and playing in a recital.

00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:38.460
Just let me know if you need anything.

00:13:38.460 --> 00:13:43.340
I will.

00:13:43.340 --> 00:13:45.340
Madam Zinia Zanza, I better work hard

00:13:45.340 --> 00:13:48.900
Do I want to impress her?

00:13:48.900 --> 00:13:50.900
Well, I better work hard.

00:13:50.900 --> 00:14:00.490
Hi, Sam.

00:14:00.490 --> 00:14:02.490
Hey, Clarissa.

00:14:02.490 --> 00:14:04.490
What's wrong? You don't look too glad to see me.

00:14:04.490 --> 00:14:06.490
It's not you, Sam. It's Madam Zinia Zanza.

00:14:06.490 --> 00:14:08.490
Is she here?

00:14:08.490 --> 00:14:10.490
Funny.

00:14:10.490 --> 00:14:12.490
Is this a bad time? You told me to come over later,

00:14:12.490 --> 00:14:14.490
and this is later.

00:14:14.490 --> 00:14:16.490
I haven't even started practicing.

00:14:16.490 --> 00:14:18.490
Then I better go.

00:14:18.490 --> 00:14:20.490
You know everyone's talking about this concert.

00:14:20.490 --> 00:14:22.490
Recital.

00:14:22.490 --> 00:14:24.490
I played at the school.

00:14:24.490 --> 00:14:26.490
Everyone's talking about it like everybody, everybody?

00:14:26.490 --> 00:14:28.490
Everybody. You better practice.

00:14:28.490 --> 00:14:30.490
See you, Clarissa.

00:14:30.490 --> 00:14:34.470
Thanks, Sam. I'll call you later.

00:14:34.470 --> 00:14:36.470
Gee, I hadn't planned on being such a hot ticket.

00:14:36.470 --> 00:14:38.470
Still, I can see it now.

00:14:38.470 --> 00:14:40.470
Me, my flute, and my adoring public.

00:14:40.470 --> 00:15:27.080
Okay.

00:15:27.080 --> 00:15:29.080
One more time.

00:15:29.080 --> 00:15:47.690
Forget about the encore.

00:15:47.690 --> 00:15:49.690
Forget about memorizing.

00:15:49.690 --> 00:16:04.100
First, I have to remember how to play.

00:16:04.100 --> 00:16:06.100
More Clarissa.

00:16:06.100 --> 00:16:08.100
Nick, after this.

00:16:08.100 --> 00:16:22.330
Come on, buck, you're blowing the gun on.

00:16:22.330 --> 00:16:42.820
Ever seen.

00:16:42.820 --> 00:16:44.820
Ever seen. It's an all-new scary tale on

00:16:44.820 --> 00:16:46.820
Are You Afraid of the Dark?

00:16:46.820 --> 00:16:48.820
Tonight on Snick.

00:16:48.820 --> 00:16:50.820
You're watching...

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:52.820
Nick!

00:16:52.820 --> 00:16:54.820
And now, back to Clarissa, explains it all.

00:16:54.820 --> 00:17:11.580
This is ridiculous.

00:17:11.580 --> 00:17:13.580
The recital is in two days.

00:17:13.580 --> 00:17:15.580
It's a piece I know I can play,

00:17:15.580 --> 00:17:22.180
but every time I try, all that comes out is...

00:17:22.180 --> 00:17:24.180
And the pressure is building like nobody's business.

00:17:24.180 --> 00:17:26.180
Dad's already invited everyone I've ever known since pre-school,

00:17:26.180 --> 00:17:28.180
plus everyone he's ever known since pre-school.

00:17:28.180 --> 00:17:30.180
And if that's not enough pressure,

00:17:30.180 --> 00:17:32.180
my mom has opened up a savings account

00:17:32.180 --> 00:17:34.180
to make a down payment for master lessons

00:17:34.180 --> 00:17:36.180
with that Madame Zinnia's ends.

00:17:36.180 --> 00:17:38.180
If she accepts me as a student.

00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:40.180
Meanwhile, I haven't even made it through the solo once.

00:17:40.180 --> 00:17:42.180
Hi, Sam.

00:17:42.180 --> 00:17:44.180
Hi, Clarissa.

00:17:44.180 --> 00:17:48.460
I hope I'm not interrupting.

00:17:48.460 --> 00:17:50.460
Nothing to interrupt.

00:17:50.460 --> 00:17:52.460
You still can't play?

00:17:52.460 --> 00:17:54.460
It's like trying to lift a ten ton boulder with my breath.

00:17:54.460 --> 00:17:56.460
It's like I haven't been trying.

00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:58.460
I've been here for hours.

00:17:58.460 --> 00:18:00.460
I mean, look at my hands.

00:18:00.460 --> 00:18:02.460
What's the problem?

00:18:02.460 --> 00:18:04.460
I can't seem to get my fingers unfrozen.

00:18:04.460 --> 00:18:06.460
I think it's all the pressure.

00:18:06.460 --> 00:18:08.460
Well, I guess it wouldn't be a great time to have more than, but...

00:18:08.460 --> 00:18:10.460
But what?

00:18:10.460 --> 00:18:12.460
My dad told me that the guy who reviews

00:18:12.460 --> 00:18:14.460
for the local entertainment section

00:18:14.460 --> 00:18:16.460
is reviewing the concert.

00:18:16.460 --> 00:18:18.460
Sorry, recital.

00:18:18.460 --> 00:18:20.460
Great.

00:18:20.460 --> 00:18:22.460
Is there anything I can do to help?

00:18:22.460 --> 00:18:24.460
I fell out the window?

00:18:24.460 --> 00:18:26.460
Okay, I can't ask you to lie.

00:18:26.460 --> 00:18:28.460
Just push me?

00:18:28.460 --> 00:18:30.460
So what do you think the problem is?

00:18:30.460 --> 00:18:32.460
Simple, Sam. I must have been in the zone

00:18:32.460 --> 00:18:34.460
and now I've fallen out of it.

00:18:34.460 --> 00:18:36.460
You were in the zone?

00:18:36.460 --> 00:18:38.460
That's what made you play solo?

00:18:38.460 --> 00:18:40.460
I can't think of any other explanation.

00:18:40.460 --> 00:18:42.460
My brain just went to that one place

00:18:42.460 --> 00:18:44.460
where I couldn't seem to make a mistake.

00:18:44.460 --> 00:18:46.460
So that's where you were that day

00:18:46.460 --> 00:18:48.460
I came in while you were playing.

00:18:48.460 --> 00:18:50.460
You didn't even know I was there.

00:18:50.460 --> 00:18:52.460
To me one weekend with foosball

00:18:52.460 --> 00:18:54.460
couldn't miss.

00:18:54.460 --> 00:18:56.460
One weekend never again?

00:18:56.460 --> 00:18:58.460
Not like that.

00:18:58.460 --> 00:19:00.460
My dad says he sees an athlete all the time.

00:19:00.460 --> 00:19:02.460
Too bad.

00:19:02.460 --> 00:19:04.460
Too bad what?

00:19:04.460 --> 00:19:06.460
It's just something uncontrollable, isn't it?

00:19:06.460 --> 00:19:08.460
I mean, you just have to wait until you get there again.

00:19:08.460 --> 00:19:10.460
Sam, I don't have time

00:19:10.460 --> 00:19:12.460
to wait for an invitation from the zone.

00:19:12.460 --> 00:19:14.460
In two days I have to give a concert.

00:19:14.460 --> 00:19:16.460
Recital.

00:19:16.460 --> 00:19:18.460
See how it's getting to me?

00:19:18.460 --> 00:19:20.460
Still.

00:19:20.460 --> 00:19:22.460
I don't know, but there must be a way.

00:19:22.460 --> 00:19:24.460
If the zone won't come to me,

00:19:24.460 --> 00:19:30.460
then I'll come to the zone.

00:19:30.460 --> 00:19:32.460
Hey, sport.

00:19:32.460 --> 00:19:34.460
What you doing?

00:19:34.460 --> 00:19:36.460
Oh, you know that sneakers to go store.

00:19:36.460 --> 00:19:38.460
Well, it needs more space, so I'm designing the left shoe.

00:19:38.460 --> 00:19:40.460
What are you going to do if they need to expand again?

00:19:40.460 --> 00:19:42.460
I'll put a pump on it.

00:19:42.460 --> 00:19:44.460
So, what do you need?

00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:46.460
Actually, Dad, I was just wondering if...

00:19:46.460 --> 00:19:51.270
Wait a minute!

00:19:51.270 --> 00:19:53.270
I just did an electromagnetic reading

00:19:53.270 --> 00:19:56.270
and they are inches away from total EMF meltdown.

00:19:56.270 --> 00:19:58.270
Well, what exactly does that mean, Ferguson?

00:19:58.270 --> 00:20:01.270
It's head to the hills, property values are plummeting.

00:20:01.270 --> 00:20:03.270
Ferguson, I just got a call from Edna's sub-restudio

00:20:03.270 --> 00:20:05.270
and she's very upset. What did you tell her?

00:20:05.270 --> 00:20:07.270
Exactly what she needed to know, Mom.

00:20:07.270 --> 00:20:10.270
Her EMF levels are beyond toxic.

00:20:10.270 --> 00:20:12.270
All they got to do is flip on their hair dryer

00:20:12.270 --> 00:20:14.270
and it could vaporize the neighborhood.

00:20:14.270 --> 00:20:16.270
She's called everyone on the block. They're all in a panic.

00:20:16.270 --> 00:20:18.270
No one should fear the truth, Mom.

00:20:18.270 --> 00:20:21.270
Are you sure you're operating that device correctly?

00:20:21.270 --> 00:20:33.200
Yeah, let me go check Dad's lamp.

00:20:33.200 --> 00:20:36.200
I thought my hands felt a little tingling.

00:20:36.200 --> 00:20:38.200
Well, it would be a hundred

00:20:38.200 --> 00:20:42.200
if it wasn't for this little tiny decimal point right here.

00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:45.200
1.00?

00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:47.200
That's in the safe range.

00:20:47.200 --> 00:20:49.200
Yeah, probably just writer's crap.

00:20:49.200 --> 00:20:51.200
Nice move, Mr. Edison.

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:53.200
Come on, Ferguson. Where are we going?

00:20:53.200 --> 00:20:56.200
Going back to the sofa scenes to straighten this out right now.

00:20:56.200 --> 00:21:00.730
Oh, Mom.

00:21:00.730 --> 00:21:03.730
The master's the higher brain functions. He could be dangerous.

00:21:03.730 --> 00:21:05.730
So, what did you need sport?

00:21:05.730 --> 00:21:07.730
You got any old incense lying around?

00:21:07.730 --> 00:21:09.730
Incense?

00:21:09.730 --> 00:21:11.730
Well, gee, I'm not sure.

00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:13.730
I've got a bunch of junk here in the cabinets.

00:21:13.730 --> 00:21:15.730
There might be some. But I doubt it.

00:21:15.730 --> 00:21:17.730
What do you need incense for?

00:21:17.730 --> 00:21:19.730
Well, I was just practicing the flute

00:21:19.730 --> 00:21:21.730
and I was having a little trouble concentrating.

00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:24.730
Uh-huh. So, what's the incense supposed to do?

00:21:24.730 --> 00:21:27.730
Well, I thought maybe it would help me get back into the zone.

00:21:27.730 --> 00:21:29.730
The zone?

00:21:29.730 --> 00:21:31.730
I hit the zone once.

00:21:31.730 --> 00:21:33.730
Back in 67.

00:21:33.730 --> 00:21:35.730
Wow, Dad, what was your calling? Music poetry?

00:21:35.730 --> 00:21:36.730
Stamping.

00:21:36.730 --> 00:21:37.730
Stamping?

00:21:37.730 --> 00:21:40.730
Stamping. Can goods. The grocery store.

00:21:40.730 --> 00:21:43.730
Yeah, I was just done a summer job or so I thought.

00:21:43.730 --> 00:21:45.730
I was in charge of stamping all the prices on all the stuff.

00:21:45.730 --> 00:21:47.730
That's when you hit your zone?

00:21:47.730 --> 00:21:49.730
Oh, yeah.

00:21:49.730 --> 00:21:51.730
Yeah, I was just stamping away, you know.

00:21:51.730 --> 00:21:53.730
49 cents, 49 cents, 49 cents,

00:21:53.730 --> 00:21:55.730
but all of a sudden, whammo.

00:21:55.730 --> 00:21:58.730
I hit a bean and bacon soup can right in the middle.

00:21:58.730 --> 00:21:59.730
Really?

00:21:59.730 --> 00:22:00.730
I mean, dead center.

00:22:00.730 --> 00:22:02.730
And then I did it again and again and again.

00:22:02.730 --> 00:22:05.730
I couldn't stop. I was a 49 cent stamping machine.

00:22:05.730 --> 00:22:07.730
I nailed every can in that place.

00:22:07.730 --> 00:22:09.730
Ah, felt great.

00:22:09.730 --> 00:22:11.730
Then what happened?

00:22:11.730 --> 00:22:12.730
I got fired.

00:22:12.730 --> 00:22:13.730
What for?

00:22:13.730 --> 00:22:16.730
Well, you know, I'd labeled everything 49 cents.

00:22:16.730 --> 00:22:18.730
Boss lost a fortune.

00:22:18.730 --> 00:22:21.730
And I never found my way back to the zone again.

00:22:21.730 --> 00:22:26.200
Well, I don't think there's any incense in here support.

00:22:26.200 --> 00:22:28.200
You can go check the attic if you want.

00:22:28.200 --> 00:22:31.200
No, thanks. I think I'm going to try something else.

00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:32.200
Good luck.

00:22:32.200 --> 00:22:33.200
Lock. Dad.

00:22:33.200 --> 00:22:35.200
Luck's the last thing I'm relying on.

00:22:35.200 --> 00:22:37.200
If I want to get back into the zone,

00:22:37.200 --> 00:22:40.200
I'm going to have to take the scientific approach.

00:22:40.200 --> 00:22:47.420
Only one more day to the performance

00:22:47.420 --> 00:22:50.420
and it looks like it's time for me to take the clinical approach.

00:22:50.420 --> 00:22:52.420
I've isolated all the major elements.

00:22:52.420 --> 00:22:54.420
Now I'm ready to compare and contrast

00:22:54.420 --> 00:22:56.420
the three known zone experiences.

00:22:56.420 --> 00:22:59.420
Theoretically speaking, there should be one common thread

00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:00.420
that unites them all.

00:23:00.420 --> 00:23:04.420
First, Sam's unexplained foosball phenomenon.

00:23:04.420 --> 00:23:06.420
Location, the Y.

00:23:06.420 --> 00:23:08.420
Environment, intense competition.

00:23:08.420 --> 00:23:11.420
Atmospheric conditions, smell of sweat socks.

00:23:11.420 --> 00:23:16.420
Case number two, Marshall Darling in his stamping stampede.

00:23:16.420 --> 00:23:18.420
Location, the grocery store.

00:23:18.420 --> 00:23:20.420
Environment, minimum wage.

00:23:20.420 --> 00:23:23.420
Atmospheric conditions, inky.

00:23:24.420 --> 00:23:28.420
Case number three, my fleeting fluid ability.

00:23:28.420 --> 00:23:30.420
Location, music class.

00:23:30.420 --> 00:23:32.420
Environment, this period.

00:23:32.420 --> 00:23:35.420
Atmospheric conditions, harmonious.

00:23:35.420 --> 00:23:38.420
What do these three zoning experiences have in common?

00:23:38.420 --> 00:23:41.420
Nothing. Science is a big fat bust.

00:23:41.420 --> 00:23:43.420
They could put a man on the moon

00:23:43.420 --> 00:23:45.420
but they can't get me out on a school auditorium stage.

00:23:45.420 --> 00:23:49.020
Hi, Sam.

00:23:49.020 --> 00:23:52.740
Hey, Clarissa.

00:23:52.740 --> 00:23:54.740
How's the scientific approach to zoning?

00:23:54.740 --> 00:23:56.740
Well, I'm still collating data

00:23:56.740 --> 00:23:58.740
and the results are inconclusive.

00:23:58.740 --> 00:24:00.740
Which means?

00:24:00.740 --> 00:24:01.740
I'm getting nowhere.

00:24:01.740 --> 00:24:03.740
I might as well just go and get this over with

00:24:03.740 --> 00:24:04.740
so everyone can forget it.

00:24:04.740 --> 00:24:07.740
That could happen if there's a fire in the school library.

00:24:07.740 --> 00:24:08.740
What do you mean?

00:24:08.740 --> 00:24:10.740
You know Dennis Krugtrotter?

00:24:10.740 --> 00:24:12.740
The audio-visual nerd?

00:24:12.740 --> 00:24:14.740
Sam, he's not.

00:24:14.740 --> 00:24:15.740
He is.

00:24:15.740 --> 00:24:17.740
Videotaping the whole recital for posterity

00:24:17.740 --> 00:24:19.740
in the school library.

00:24:19.740 --> 00:24:21.740
You'll be immortalized.

00:24:21.740 --> 00:24:23.740
Oh, no. That's just great.

00:24:23.740 --> 00:24:25.740
Now, anytime anyone has a free period

00:24:25.740 --> 00:24:27.740
they can just take me out of the library stacks,

00:24:27.740 --> 00:24:29.740
cram me into a VCR

00:24:29.740 --> 00:24:31.740
and watch me over and over and over again.

00:24:31.740 --> 00:24:33.740
Talk about eternal embarrassment.

00:24:33.740 --> 00:24:35.740
I've got an idea.

00:24:35.740 --> 00:24:36.740
Let's go for a walk.

00:24:36.740 --> 00:24:38.740
What? Sam, now?

00:24:38.740 --> 00:24:40.740
Hey, it'll help you clear your head.

00:24:40.740 --> 00:24:42.740
You've been cooped up in here too long to find your zone.

00:24:42.740 --> 00:24:43.740
Well...

00:24:43.740 --> 00:24:45.740
The great outdoors have inspired artists for generations.

00:24:45.740 --> 00:24:49.740
Thoreau, Van Gogh, Rambo...

00:24:49.740 --> 00:24:52.740
Well, I guess it's worth a shot.

00:24:52.740 --> 00:24:54.740
But I'm taking my flute with me.

00:24:54.740 --> 00:24:55.740
Who knows?

00:24:55.740 --> 00:24:56.740
Maybe a little bit of fresh air

00:24:56.740 --> 00:24:58.740
will make finding my zone a breeze.

00:24:58.740 --> 00:25:00.740
Na-na-na-na-na-na.

00:25:00.740 --> 00:25:03.740
Eight, nine, ten.

00:25:03.740 --> 00:25:05.740
Alright, ten invoices.

00:25:05.740 --> 00:25:08.740
Ten neighbors, multiplied by ten bucks a piece.

00:25:08.740 --> 00:25:12.740
Looks like Mr. Ben Franklin's coming to our house.

00:25:12.740 --> 00:25:14.740
Bergface, what are you doing?

00:25:14.740 --> 00:25:15.740
Hey.

00:25:15.740 --> 00:25:16.740
Congratulations.

00:25:16.740 --> 00:25:18.740
Your home has been registered E-M-F-free

00:25:18.740 --> 00:25:22.740
by a nearly certified electromagnetic particle wave technician.

00:25:22.740 --> 00:25:23.740
That's you.

00:25:23.740 --> 00:25:24.740
That's me.

00:25:24.740 --> 00:25:26.740
Hey, somebody had to do it.

00:25:26.740 --> 00:25:27.740
Do what?

00:25:27.740 --> 00:25:29.740
You mean you actually went to every house in this block

00:25:29.740 --> 00:25:31.740
with mom's electromagnetic thingy?

00:25:31.740 --> 00:25:33.740
I was much more comprehensive than that.

00:25:33.740 --> 00:25:35.740
I did a sweep from the backyard.

00:25:35.740 --> 00:25:38.740
I saved the neighbor.

00:25:38.740 --> 00:25:40.740
Yeah, tell me, that isn't worth ten bucks.

00:25:40.740 --> 00:25:44.740
Come on, Sam. Let's go find a furg for his own.

00:25:44.740 --> 00:25:52.510
Well, getting out of the house didn't get me out of my flu problem.

00:25:52.510 --> 00:25:55.510
I tried looking for inspiration in a bunch of different locations,

00:25:55.510 --> 00:25:59.510
but everything was just a little off-key.

00:25:59.510 --> 00:26:01.510
First I got my act together and took it on the road.

00:26:01.510 --> 00:26:03.510
Well, the front yard anyway.

00:26:03.510 --> 00:26:06.510
I found a face full of nature with no zone.

00:26:06.510 --> 00:26:08.510
I have a sprinkler!

00:26:08.510 --> 00:26:11.510
So then I went further to find my zone in the park.

00:26:11.510 --> 00:26:15.510
I didn't hit a single high note.

00:26:15.510 --> 00:26:20.660
But I did make 35 cents, so it wasn't a total loss.

00:26:20.660 --> 00:26:25.160
Finally I gave up on nature and went to the auditorium.

00:26:25.160 --> 00:26:29.160
That's what was to be the scene of my public humiliation in less than 24 hours.

00:26:29.160 --> 00:26:32.160
I got through my song. It even turns out I've got a fan, sort of.

00:26:32.160 --> 00:26:35.160
Hey, if you like flute playing, you ought to come back tomorrow.

00:26:35.160 --> 00:26:38.160
There's a girl about your age supposed to be playing.

00:26:38.160 --> 00:26:41.160
And I hear she's really good.

00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:47.160
Yeah, he hears I'm good till he hears me play.

00:26:48.160 --> 00:26:50.160
Hi, Sam.

00:26:50.160 --> 00:26:55.720
Hey, Clarissa. Sounds kind of quiet up here.

00:26:55.720 --> 00:26:58.720
Yeah, too quiet. Nothing works, Sam. Nothing.

00:26:58.720 --> 00:27:01.720
I know there's a way back into the zone. I just have to find it.

00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:03.720
Clarissa, we've tried everything.

00:27:03.720 --> 00:27:06.720
I know. It's been awful. I can't even look at this thing anymore.

00:27:06.720 --> 00:27:09.720
And I used to have so much fun just playing.

00:27:09.720 --> 00:27:12.720
Those were the days. Well, day, actually.

00:27:12.720 --> 00:27:14.720
So what was different about that day?

00:27:14.720 --> 00:27:18.720
Well, nobody had any expectations. And I didn't have any expectations.

00:27:18.720 --> 00:27:21.720
I just hit the zone and I was terrific.

00:27:21.720 --> 00:27:24.720
You know, even when you're not in the zone, you're pretty good.

00:27:24.720 --> 00:27:26.720
I don't want to be as good as I can be.

00:27:26.720 --> 00:27:27.720
Who doesn't?

00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:30.720
But maybe it isn't realistic to think I'll always be in the zone.

00:27:30.720 --> 00:27:34.720
I mean, Michael Jordan probably has his off days, but he still suits up, right?

00:27:34.720 --> 00:27:35.720
Yeah.

00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:38.720
So what if I do mess up? So what? Who cares? What are they going to do?

00:27:38.720 --> 00:27:39.720
Shoot me?

00:27:39.720 --> 00:27:41.720
I don't think anyone's going to shoot you, Clarissa.

00:27:41.720 --> 00:27:44.720
And forget about this pressure from my parents and Madam Zinnia Zanz

00:27:44.720 --> 00:27:47.720
and Dennis Krugtrider in his video recorder.

00:27:47.720 --> 00:27:50.720
I don't care about the zone. I'm not playing for anybody.

00:27:50.720 --> 00:27:52.720
You mean you're not going to do it?

00:27:52.720 --> 00:27:54.720
I mean, I'm not playing for anybody but me.

00:27:57.720 --> 00:28:00.720
Clarissa, we were very proud of you tonight.

00:28:00.720 --> 00:28:02.720
Didn't you enjoy watching your sister play?

00:28:02.720 --> 00:28:05.720
